    {
      "id": "b239b17070fc2b980994e14525ea1f4d",
      "url": "https://crazierl.org/demo/",
      "title": "Show HN: Crazierl \u2013 An Erlang Operating System",
      "content": "<p>Crazierl is an experimental/hobby operating system based around BEAM.<p>I've linked the browser based demo; I don\u2019t recommend using a phone; it does work, slowly, on the phones I tested, but it\u2019s very awkward to use. You can share a link with a hashtag with your friends and click the consent checkbox, and it (should) link up into dist and I\u2019ve also included a chat application you can start with chat:start(). (quit chat with /quit, or use the shell menu with ctrl-g to switch between shells etc).<p>The browser demo relies on the v86 javascript x86 virtual machine. You can also run Crazierl on a real x86 system, but I\u2019ve had mixed luck on modern systems, it uses some esoteric legacy VGA features and support for that isn\u2019t getting better.<p>Crazierl is fairly limited: 32-bit x86, BIOS boot, only two NIC drivers virtio-net and realtek 8168. But it's got enough to become part of an Erlang dist cluster. It also supports SMP, but it\u2019s crashy with high core counts in qemu; there\u2019s almost certainly several concurrency bugs in the kernel. There's also a lot of excess tcp debug spew (sorry).<p>Source code is available (Apache) <a href=\"https://github.com/russor/crazierl/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/russor/crazierl/</a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47567049\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47567049</a></p>\n<p>Points: 6</p>\n<p># Comments: 2</p>",
